expression: "snapshot(&[\"ralph\", \"--help\"])"
---
Run an AI agent loop to implement a change

Iteratively runs an AI coding agent (OpenCode, Claude, etc.) to implement
a change proposal. Monitors progress and commits incrementally.

Examples:
  ito ralph --change 005-01_add-auth
  ito ralph --change 005-01_add-auth --harness claude --max-iterations 5

Usage: ito ralph [OPTIONS] [PROMPT]...

Arguments:
  [PROMPT]...
          Prompt text

Options:
  -c, --change <CHANGE>
          Target a specific change

      --no-color
          Disable color output

      --help-all
          Print the full CLI reference (equivalent to `ito help --all`)

  -m, --module <MODULE>
          Target a module.

          Note: when running with `--no-interactive`, `--module` implies `--continue-module`.

      --continue-module
          When using --module, keep working through ready changes until module work is complete

      --continue-ready
          Keep working through eligible changes across the repo until work is complete

      --harness <HARNESS>
          Harness to run

          [default: opencode]
          [possible values: opencode, claude, codex, copilot]

      --model <MODEL>
          Model id for the harness

      --min-iterations <MIN_ITERATIONS>
          Minimum iterations before stopping

          [default: 1]

      --max-iterations <MAX_ITERATIONS>
          Maximum iterations (default: unlimited)

      --completion-promise <COMPLETION_PROMISE>
          Completion promise token

          [default: COMPLETE]

      --skip-validation
          Skip completion validation (tasks + project checks/tests)

          When set, Ralph trusts the completion promise and exits immediately.

      --validation-command <VALIDATION_COMMAND>
          Extra validation command to run on completion promise

          Runs after the project validation steps.

      --exit-on-error
          Exit Ralph immediately if harness exits non-zero

      --error-threshold <ERROR_THRESHOLD>
          Maximum non-zero harness exits before failing (default: 10)

      --allow-all
          Allow all tool actions (dangerous)

      --no-commit
          Do not create git commits per iteration

      --status
          Show current Ralph state for the change

      --add-context <ADD_CONTEXT>
          Append extra context to the Ralph loop

      --clear-context
          Clear the Ralph loop context file

      --no-interactive
          Do not prompt for selections

  -v, --verbose
          Verbose output

      --timeout <TIMEOUT>
          Inactivity timeout (e.g. 15m)

      --file <FILE>
          Read prompt text from a file

      --prd <FILE>
          Read pending tasks from a markdown PRD file

      --yaml <FILE>
          Read pending tasks from a YAML task file

      --github <REPO>
          Read pending tasks from GitHub issues in owner/repo form

      --github-label <LABEL>
          Filter GitHub issue task sources by label

      --sync-issue <NUMBER>
          Sync a markdown PRD file into a GitHub issue body after completion

      --branch-per-task
          Create a dedicated git branch for the current task before running Ralph

      --base-branch <BRANCH>
          Base branch used when creating task branches

      --create-pr
          Create a pull request after successful task completion

      --draft-pr
          Create pull requests as drafts

      --browser
          Enable browser automation guidance when supported tools are available

      --notify
          Emit an operator notification after the run completes or fails

      --parallel
          Execute external task-source work in parallel worker loops

      --max-parallel <MAX_PARALLEL>
          Maximum number of concurrent parallel Ralph workers

          [default: 3]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
